---
description: Use current official documentation for dependencies
alwaysApply: true
---

Before implementing tasks involving external libraries or frameworks:

1. Check the installed package version in package.json and lock files.
2. Use official documentation for that exact major version.
3. Prefer @Docs or @Web when API behavior may have changed.
4. Do not rely only on model memory for library APIs.
5. Before editing, briefly state:
   - detected package version
   - documentation source used
   - any relevant breaking changes
